Dedupe cmap subtables before saving.

For the Windows target, add_cmap_platform_3_encoding_10() appends a (3,10)
format-12 subtable, then ensure_windows_cmap() converts the existing (3,4)
subtable in place to another (3,10) format-12 subtable. That leaves two
subtables sharing (platformID, platEncID, language) == (3, 10, 0), which
newer fontTools rejects at compile time:

  ValueError: cmap subtables have duplicate (platformID, platEncID,
  language) entries, which the OpenType spec does not allow: {(3, 10, 0)}

Drop duplicate (platformID, platEncID, language) subtables, keeping the
first, right before the font is written.

--- a/convert.py
+++ b/convert.py
@@ -104,6 +104,15 @@ def main() -> int:
     add_cmap_platform_3_encoding_10(font)
     if is_windows:
         apply_windows_compat(font)

+    _seen = set()
+    _kept = []
+    for _t in font["cmap"].tables:
+        _key = (_t.platformID, _t.platEncID, _t.language)
+        if _key in _seen:
+            continue
+        _seen.add(_key)
+        _kept.append(_t)
+    font["cmap"].tables = _kept
     args.output.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
     font.save(args.output)
     LOG.info("Wrote %s", args.output)
